        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 28 at 6:00PM CDT until May 28 at 6:15PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 600 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 10 miles northwest
of Knowles, or 13 miles northeast of Beaver, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Tennis ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.
People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles.

Locations impacted include...
Mocane, Forgan, and Knowles.
</description>
        <instruction>A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for the Panhandle
of Oklahoma.

For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
